		<body>
			<pb n="1"/>
				<p rend="align(center)"><hi rend="underline">The Angel &#38; the Child</hi></p>
				<p>&#8220;Thou art too beautiful &#38; good&#44;</p>
				<p>&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;Too full of sacred mirth&#44;</p>
				<p>Too pensive in they gayest mood&#44;</p>
				<p>&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;Dear child for this cold earth.&#8221;</p>
				<p></p>
				<p>Thus spake an angel to a child</p>
				<p>&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;And fanned with softest breath</p>
				<p>His tender cheeks&#44; and eyelids mild&#44;</p>
				<p>&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;That angel&#39;s name was <hi rend="underline">Death</hi>.</p>
				<p></p>
				<p>The angel with his folded wings&#44;</p>
				<p>&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;And torch inverted stands</p>
				<p>And whispers to the child &#38; sings</p>
				<p>&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;And holds its little hands.</p>
				<p></p>
				<p>The children by the cottage door</p>
				<p>&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;See not the wondrous sight</p>
				<p>But think their brother&#39;s eyes before</p>
				<p>&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;Have never looked so bright.</p>
				<p></p>
				<p>Oh&#33; <persName>Herbert</persName> darling&#33;  <persName>Herbert</persName> love&#33;</p>
				<p>&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;What is it thou doest see&#63;</p>
				<p>Why dost thou smile &#38; look above</p>
				<p>&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;And move from off my knee.</p>
				<p></p>
				<p>My brother dearest&#44; let me go&#44;</p>
				<p>&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;My brothers sisters dear</p>
				<p>Detain me not&#44; nor weep with wo</p>
				<p>&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;There is no cause for fear.</p>
				<p></p>
			<pb n="2"/>
				<p>Oh&#33;  Didst thou not&#44; my mother&#44; see</p>
				<p>&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;The Messenger divine</p>
				<p>That took me gently from thy knee</p>
				<p>&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;And said I was not thine.</p>
				<p></p>
				<p>He spake of all the flowers that bloom</p>
				<p>&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;Like glittering stars above&#59;</p>
				<p>of wondrous things beyond the tomb</p>
				<p>&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;But most he spake of Love.</p>
				<p></p>
				<p>He said it was the brightest thing</p>
				<p>&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;That shone in that bright sphere&#44;</p>
				<p>That&#44; from the seraphs harps one string</p>
				<p>&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;Still vibrates even here.</p>
				<p></p>
				<p>&#8220;Thou dearest child what heavenly light</p>
				<p>&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;Is beaming round thy face</p>
				<p>What anguish will be mine this night</p>
				<p>&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;To see thy empty place&#8221;.</p>
				<p></p>
				<p>Oh&#33;  Mother&#44; if thou couldst but see</p>
				<p>&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;Thy angel by my side</p>
				<p>How lovingly his clasping me</p>
				<p>&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;Thy tears would soon be dried.</p>
				<p></p>
				<p>Oh&#33; if thou couldst but hear his voice</p>
				<p>&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;So gentle and so mild&#44;</p>
				<p>Just now he whispered me &#8220;rejoice&#44;</p>
				<p>&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;Rejoice thou blessed child&#8221;.</p>
				<p></p>
			<pb n="3"/>
				<p>For thou to Paradise doest go&#44;</p>
				<p>&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;Yes&#44; thou hast reached that goal</p>
				<p>Before one pang of earthly woe</p>
				<p>&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;Has touched thy sinless soul.</p>
				<p>&#8212;&#8212;&#8212;&#8212;&#8212;&#8212; <persName role="author">R. E. S.</persName></p>
				<p rend="align(right)"><placeName><hi rend="underline">Heidelberg</hi></placeName></p>
				<p>I hope you will be able to decipher<lb/> this&#8212;my pen &#38; ink were not good<lb/> which is excuse for bad writing.<lb/>  Can you tell me why we do not keep<lb/> <hi rend="underline">our <date>New Year</date> in <date>April</date></hi>&#63;  Exodus XII. 2. &#38; 18.<lb/> also Leviticus XXIII.5.</p>
				<p>Will you be so kind as to explain this to me<lb/> &#38; please also to tell me if you have yet<lb/> met with much success in the<lb/> disposal of your Bible.</p>
				<p>I continue writing my Prayers&#8212;</p>
			<pb n="4"/>
				<p>I had almost forgotten to tell you&#44; my dear friend&#44;<lb/> that I sent a copy of my Poems to His Majesty the <persName>King</persName><lb/> <placeName>Bavaria</placeName>&#44; who is himself a Poet&#8212;&#38; I received by <hi rend="underline">return</hi><lb/> <hi rend="underline">of Post</hi> a most polite answer with many expressions<lb/> of thanks&#8212;I am sure you will be pleased to<lb/> hear this.</p>
				<p><hi rend="underline">Voie d&#39;Angletore</hi></p>
				<p><hi rend="underline">Paid</hi></p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">The <addressee>Revd I. Leeser</addressee></p>
			<p rend="indent(1)"><placeName>371 Walnut Street</placeName></p>
			<p rend="indent(2)"><placeName>Philadelphia</placeName></p>
			<p rend="indent(2)"><placeName>America</placeName></p>
				<p><date>March 11th</date></p>
				<p><date>1855</date></p>
			
